   <refnamediv>
       <refname>bino_rnd </refname>
               <refpurpose>binomial random draws </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[rnd]=bino_rnd(N,p,r,c)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> N </term> =    the # of trials (scalar)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> p </term> =    the probability of success (scalar)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> n </term> =    number of trials (scalar)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> r,c </term> =    size of random sample from binominal(N,p) distribution (optional; default  =   1,1)</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> rnd </term> =   (rxc) matrix of random draws from the binomial (N,p) distribution, equal to the number of successes in n-trials</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Random sampling from a binomial distribution.
<para>  NOTE: mean = a/(a+b), variance = ab/((a+b)*(a+b)*(a+b+1))  </para>
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
x= bino_rnd(15,0.25,4,3)
// Provides a (4x3) matrix of random draws from the binomial(5,15) law.
x= bino_rnd(15,0.25)
// Provides a scalar drawn for the same law.
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
